Combined with Eq. (2) [34,35], QD denotes the quantum yield of the donor, n represents the refractive index of the medium, κ2 signifies the dipolar orientation factor between the two fluorescent proteins, NA corresponds to Avogadro's constant, εA indicates the maximum extinction coefficient of the acceptor, and J (
                           λ
                        ) represents the spectral overlap integral between the normalized donor emission spectrum FD and the acceptor absorption spectrum EA [36]. In summary, the FRET efficiency is primarily determined by the donor’s quantum yield and the spectral overlap between the donor emission spectrum and the acceptor excitation spectrum.
